Description: 
        Grey: Black, but brighter, but not as bright as White (arbitrarilyâ€“inspired)
        ============================================================================
        
        `Black <https://github.com/ambv/black>`_ is an amazing tool for autoâ€“formatting
        Python code in a style that I don't really care about, but I like consistency,
        so I use it in all my projects.
        
        It has **one** configuration option â€” to change its default lineâ€“length of ``88``
        chars to, say, ``120``, like I like.
        
        -----------
        
        That is *exactly* what **grey** does. It invokes ``$ black --line-length 120`` on your behalf.
        
        
        Usage
        =====
        
        ::
        
            $ grey myapp.py
            reformatted myapp.py
        
        
        
        Installation
        ============
        
        ::
        
        	$ pipenv install white
